# Computer Network – Syllabus

## Course Distribution

**70% Coverage:** Introduction to Computer Network, Physical Layer, Data Link Layer, Network Layer
**30% Coverage:** Transport Layer, Application Layer

## 1. Introduction to Computer Network

* History / Need of CN
* Network Models: OSI, TCP/IP
* Introduction to OSI Model
* Functions of each layer
* Introduction to TCP/IP Model
* Introduction to IP and its supporting protocols
* Introduction to TCP

## 2. Physical Layer

* Introduction to Signals: Analog (Period, Frequency, Amplitude), Digital (Bit)
* Signal Encoding Techniques
* Bandwidth, Throughput and Delay (Numericals)
* Multiplexing: FDM, WDM, TDM

## 3. Data Link Layer

* Error Detection vs Correction
* Logic for Error Detection
* Hamming Distance / Minimum Hamming Distance
* Linear Block Codes: Simple Parity Check Code, 2D Parity, CRC, Checksum, Hamming Code
* Framing
* Flow and Error Control: Stop and Wait, Go Back N, Selective Repeat, Sliding Window



